Summary
Added a new reusable script SCCMClient_Remediation_Remote.ps1 that is designed specifically for corrupted SCCM client recovery, including uninstall, cleanup, reinstall, and post-install validation flow. 

Added remote execution support using Invoke-Command so you can target specific devices with -ComputerName (and optional -Credential) instead of logging in manually. 

Added safer operational controls:

Parameterized site settings (-SiteCode, -DnsSuffix, source/local paths). 

Structured logging per endpoint in C:\Windows\Temp\SCCM_Remediation_<Computer>.log. 

Best-effort wrapper for non-critical operations to reduce hard-fail interruptions. 

Optional WMI repository verification/salvage for corruption cases via -RepairWmi. 

Added post-install health actions: SCCM site assignment check, machine policy triggers, and optional gpupdate control (-SkipGpupdate). 

How to run remotely for certain devices (example):

# Single device
.\SCCMClient_Remediation_Remote.ps1 -ComputerName PC-1234 -RepairWmi

# Multiple devices
.\SCCMClient_Remediation_Remote.ps1 -ComputerName PC-1234,PC-5678 -RepairWmi

# With explicit credentials
$cred = Get-Credential
.\SCCMClient_Remediation_Remote.ps1 -ComputerName PC-1234 -Credential $cred -RepairWmi
